The article discusses the APEC Leaders' Growth Strategy, which focuses on achieving balanced, inclusive, sustainable, innovative, and secure growth in the Asia-Pacific region. The strategy recognizes the changing economic environment and the need to address challenges such as climate change, natural disasters, terrorism, and food insecurity. The strategy includes an action plan that outlines specific steps to be taken in areas such as structural reform, human resource and entrepreneurship development, green growth, knowledge-based economy, and human security. APEC Senior Officials will be responsible for implementing the action plan and conducting annual progress reviews. The progress of the strategy will be reported to APEC Leaders in 2015.